1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:29,980
The speaker quotes Scripture, tells stories, and uses proper punctuation, capitalization,

2
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:36,030
Well, Fullerton took third in the golf tournament.

3
00:00:36,510 --> 00:00:38,090
We got a trophy, folks.

4
00:00:40,450 --> 00:00:42,670
Thanks to Kent and myself.

5
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:48,350
I didn't really contribute much, but Jeff Templeton and his friend was a ringer, and we got Jeff.

6
00:00:48,410 --> 00:00:50,370
And we just loaded this team so we could win.

7
00:00:51,030 --> 00:00:59,170
And it's getting personal because, see, South Shores Church, Ty Guy, one of our sister churches, they took second.

8
00:00:59,170 --> 00:01:02,510
and so next year it's really personal

9
00:01:02,510 --> 00:01:05,530
because he's so cocky down there

10
00:01:05,530 --> 00:01:09,290
and I've just wanted for years to just get my little trophy

11
00:01:09,290 --> 00:01:12,390
now that we got the trophy my goal is to beat Ty Guy

12
00:01:12,390 --> 00:01:15,090
so we're going to work at it, you're going to pray

13
00:01:15,090 --> 00:01:17,650
and if you've got any golf skills you let us know

14
00:01:17,650 --> 00:01:20,670
because Fullerton must trump South Shores

15
00:01:20,670 --> 00:01:24,040
God is good and those are fun things

16
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:26,120
and I hope you can be a part of stuff like that

17
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,340
we're going to have more fun the coming weeks including this morning

18
00:01:29,340 --> 00:01:37,970
because we're going to talk about giving. Isn't that fun? Amen, it is. I believe that giving is fun.

19
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:46,260
I didn't always think that way. In fact, I used to be very uncomfortable and embarrassed

20
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:55,940
to talk about money from the pulpit. The scandal of the 80s and all those things tainted my ability

21
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:58,020
to come at the text fresh

22
00:01:58,020 --> 00:01:59,800
and preach it with vigor.

23
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:02,700
And I have repented of that.

24
00:02:03,460 --> 00:02:04,240
Here's why.

25
00:02:04,540 --> 00:02:07,460
Because the Bible is on my side.

26
00:02:08,730 --> 00:02:11,070
It's all over the Scriptures.

27
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:14,250
And therefore, I now enjoy

28
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:16,010
preaching about money and tithing

29
00:02:16,010 --> 00:02:16,690
and stewardship

30
00:02:16,690 --> 00:02:20,070
because God's Word is on my side.

31
00:02:20,980 --> 00:02:22,260
If you don't like it,

32
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,220
take it up with God.

33
00:02:25,030 --> 00:02:26,310
It's His problem.

34
00:02:26,670 --> 00:02:32,020
In all seriousness, the Bible says so much about a lot of topics.

35
00:02:32,380 --> 00:02:36,680
There are 500 verses on faith, more or less.

36
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:41,140
There's less than 500 verses on prayer.

37
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:49,420
But there's more than 2,000 verses on the issue of money and what we do with our money.

38
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:51,760
Why is that?

39
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:58,320
Why does the Bible talk so much about our money and what we do with it?

40
00:02:59,170 --> 00:03:02,390
I think the Bible talks so much about our use of money

41
00:03:02,390 --> 00:03:08,770
because the use of our money is reflective of the state of our heart.

42
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,500
Does that make sense?

43
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:16,480
How we use our money is reflective of the state of our heart.

44
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:21,560
What our heart beats for is reflected in what we write checks for.

45
00:03:23,990 --> 00:03:27,450
What we get charged up about is what we charge.

46
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:32,550
Are you charged up about God's kingdom?

47
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:38,320
If you are, you will give willingly to the Lord.

48
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:44,670
Your pocketbook is a theological document

49
00:03:44,670 --> 00:03:49,260
because it reflects what's in your heart.

50
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:55,880
Jesus knew the state of our heart is clearly seen

51
00:03:55,880 --> 00:04:03,640
through the lens of how we use our money, and that's why the Bible talks so openly and freely

52
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:09,840
about money, and if the Bible talks about money, then I'm going to preach about it because I'm a

53
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:19,400
biblical preacher. So here we go. First of all, the goal of the Christian life is to live by faith

54
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:25,940
and to live in obedience to God, and that's a refining of our character that it would be like

55
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:35,960
Jesus Christ. We are to be like little Christs. Little Christs. And we're to become like God in

56
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:46,640
our character. We're to live our lives as Jesus would live our lives. Think about that for a

57
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:54,120
moment. Live your life as Jesus would live your life. If Jesus was born into your circumstances

58
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:59,680
with your situation, your background, your physical characteristics, and so forth.

59
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:02,680
How would Jesus live your life?

60
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:10,870
We want our lives to be how Jesus would live our life.

61
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:14,540
That is the issue of spiritual formation.

62
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:18,380
Forming our spirits to be like Jesus Christ.

63
00:05:18,380 --> 00:05:22,620
That our heart would be like the heart and soul of Jesus Christ.

64
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:26,780
and one of the key issues in becoming more Christ-like

65
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:30,060
is that we take on his selflessness.

66
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:36,100
For Jesus, friends, is the image of the invisible God

67
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,780
and he gave his very life for us

68
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:43,000
and it's God's very nature to give.

69
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:45,990
If we're going to be Christ-like,

70
00:05:45,990 --> 00:05:48,130
we must become givers.

71
00:05:49,470 --> 00:05:50,510
We must become givers.

72
00:05:52,780 --> 00:05:54,000
We all know the verse

73
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,530
and we need to see it again.

74
00:05:57,050 --> 00:05:59,570
For God so loved the world

75
00:05:59,570 --> 00:06:00,850
that He did what?

76
00:06:01,090 --> 00:06:03,890
That He gave His only Son

77
00:06:03,890 --> 00:06:07,350
so that everyone who believes in Him

78
00:06:07,350 --> 00:06:11,330
will not perish but have eternal life.

79
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,540
Isn't that wonderful?

80
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:14,280
Amen.

81
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,540
God gave of Himself

82
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:19,200
that we might have eternal life.

83
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:21,680
That's the heart of our God.

84
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,200
A God who gives.

85
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:28,820
If I want to be like Christ, I must learn to give.

86
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,480
Giving makes us like God.

87
00:06:33,890 --> 00:06:35,890
As I've studied this issue of giving,

88
00:06:37,930 --> 00:06:44,910
I realize that giving is more than just transferring money to a church budget.

89
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:52,670
As I look at the Apostle Paul and how he looks at giving throughout the New Testament,

90
00:06:53,170 --> 00:06:56,750
I notice a variety of descriptions about giving.

91
00:06:56,750 --> 00:07:00,110
He talks about it in terms of a collection.

92
00:07:00,970 --> 00:07:03,410
He talks about giving in terms of blessing,

93
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:06,390
in terms of a priestly service.

94
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:11,160
He talks about it in terms of sharing and fellowship

95
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:13,920
and serving and grace.

96
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,440
And I've come away to realize

97
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:20,140
that really giving has many textures of meaning,

98
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:24,500
and yet all those meanings have nothing really to do

99
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,400
with the language of money.

100
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:35,360
Those words I shared with you come from meaning as it relates to relationship.

101
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:40,230
Paul looks at giving in terms of relationship.

102
00:07:40,990 --> 00:07:42,350
It's not about budgets.

103
00:07:42,970 --> 00:07:46,310
It's about relationship and the state of our heart.

104
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:55,530
When we grow, or rather we let grace grow in our lives,

105
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:59,950
we become more like Jesus, more like little Christs.

106
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:03,790
and I have to say friends that God has forgiven my sins

107
00:08:03,790 --> 00:08:07,330
he has begun a process of cleaning me up

108
00:08:07,330 --> 00:08:10,730
he has given me the Holy Spirit for powerful living

109
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:13,990
and I can stand and say that I am incredibly blessed

110
00:08:13,990 --> 00:08:16,590
and I want my life to count

111
00:08:16,590 --> 00:08:18,370
I want to live for him

112
00:08:18,370 --> 00:08:21,250
and I know that you do as well

113
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:24,500
and therefore you want to be people

114
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:27,430
that are rich givers

115
00:08:27,430 --> 00:08:29,890
like the character of our God

116
00:08:29,890 --> 00:08:35,490
it's a thrill to live a life for the Lord

117
00:08:35,490 --> 00:08:38,850
and giving becomes part of that journey

118
00:08:38,850 --> 00:08:43,850
friends are we getting motivated are we getting a little bit excited

119
00:08:43,850 --> 00:08:46,750
because we've got to really embrace this

120
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:51,830
and I hope that my yelling and ranting and raving gets you a little bit excited

121
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:56,170
to take a journey with Christ in terms of giving faithfully

122
00:08:56,170 --> 00:08:58,590
and abundantly from your hearts

123
00:08:59,770 --> 00:09:03,130
I hope the Spirit captures your spirit today.

124
00:09:04,010 --> 00:09:08,530
There's a lot of reasons and a lot of motivations for giving.

125
00:09:08,950 --> 00:09:11,230
And I'm going to explore those this morning.

126
00:09:11,230 --> 00:09:15,470
The first one, starting from the lowest form to the highest.

127
00:09:17,490 --> 00:09:19,950
There's a motivation we can lay out there for giving.

128
00:09:20,430 --> 00:09:22,820
The first one is guilt.

129
00:09:24,410 --> 00:09:28,410
I can just lay big trips on you.

130
00:09:28,410 --> 00:09:31,590
and we can give out of guilt.

131
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:36,590
It's the most base level motivation.

132
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:40,510
You do it because you have to do it.

133
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:47,450
Usher comes by, that plate comes by,

134
00:09:48,970 --> 00:09:50,250
you haven't put anything in it,

135
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,460
and if I've guilted you effectively,

136
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:57,060
you'll think something like this.

137
00:09:58,910 --> 00:10:01,150
He knows I haven't put anything in in three months.

138
00:10:01,690 --> 00:10:04,080
He keeps coming to my aisle.

139
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:06,590
All right, fine, just make him go away.

140
00:10:06,670 --> 00:10:15,940
fine here's 20 bucks it's in I've done it now go away ha it's over we can do

141
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:21,920
that I can send the ushers to come back to you over and over we can do all kinds

142
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:30,340
of things the problem is friends that guilt-giving is not biblical it's not an

143
00:10:30,340 --> 00:10:37,070
attitude that Scripture elucidates in any way notice this verse 2nd Corinthians

144
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:40,830
chapter 9, verse 7. Paul says, you must each

145
00:10:40,830 --> 00:10:44,970
make up your own mind as to how much you should

146
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:49,010
give. Don't give reluctantly or in response to

147
00:10:49,010 --> 00:10:52,720
pressure, for God loves the person who gives

148
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:58,260
cheerfully. It's not about guilt. Giving

149
00:10:58,260 --> 00:11:02,300
is supposed to be cheerful. At least do it

150
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:08,400
with a smile. How often do you smile when the plate comes by?

151
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:09,760
Let's be honest.

152
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:11,820
We're a little bit dour about giving around here.

153
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:16,530
It's kind of, there it is, pass it on by.

154
00:11:18,090 --> 00:11:19,770
What if we were to just get excited?

155
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:23,600
And maybe in your own place, in your own pew, just say,

156
00:11:23,860 --> 00:11:25,900
thank you, Lord, for all that you've given to me.

157
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,000
Here we go.

158
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:28,960
Wouldn't that be different?

159
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:30,920
With a smile.

160
00:11:32,380 --> 00:11:33,640
It's supposed to be fun.

161
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:42,110
Now, the good thing about guilt giving is the money still comes to the church.

162
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:44,880
You see, it still comes in.

163
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:49,220
Whether you give it with a smile or out of guilt, it still comes in.

164
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:51,020
It still pays the bills.

165
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,580
That's the strength of guilt giving.

166
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,400
And let's be honest.

167
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:59,840
The reality is it takes money to keep this going.

168
00:12:00,610 --> 00:12:01,530
It really does.

169
00:12:01,530 --> 00:12:09,630
In fact, it's something like $12,000 a week to make this place hum and run to bless people, including yourselves.

170
00:12:10,550 --> 00:12:11,330
That's a lot of money.

171
00:12:12,870 --> 00:12:13,930
That's why we need to give.

172
00:12:14,110 --> 00:12:16,630
And if you give out of guilt, we'll still take it, all right?

173
00:12:21,290 --> 00:12:22,970
But it's the lowest form.

174
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:27,280
It's not a biblical way to give.

175
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:32,860
And I want you to rise out of guilt giving and give out of your heart and with joy

176
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:38,800
because you want to be a blessing to the Lord because the Lord has been a blessing to you.

177
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:45,500
You see, the problem with guilt giving is it's joyless.

178
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:49,580
it produces no spiritual fruit in your life

179
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:55,210
it doesn't show any progress as we try and chip away

180
00:12:55,210 --> 00:13:00,710
at materialism in our culture it doesn't do anything to our spirit

181
00:13:00,710 --> 00:13:03,530
really it doesn't do anything and perhaps

182
00:13:03,530 --> 00:13:06,990
except make you bitter we'll take your money

183
00:13:06,990 --> 00:13:09,770
but you'll leave bitter that's not a good thing

184
00:13:09,770 --> 00:13:13,080
and it's not biblical and that's not of god

185
00:13:14,300 --> 00:13:15,900
So guilt is out.

186
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:18,850
Next level, we'll step it up one.

187
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:22,610
Another motivation for giving is responsibility.

188
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:28,100
And there's a passage I'd like to share with you from 2 Corinthians 8.

189
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:31,360
If you'd like to follow along in your Bibles or watch the screen,

190
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:35,700
we're going to read this one section, verses 1 to 15.

191
00:13:36,770 --> 00:13:37,390
Paul writes,

192
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:42,400
Now I want to tell you, dear brothers and sisters,

193
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:48,810
what God in his kindness has done for the churches in Macedonia.

194
00:13:50,020 --> 00:13:53,720
Though they have been going through many trouble and hard times,

195
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:59,780
their wonderful joy and deep poverty has overflowed in rich generosity.

196
00:14:01,180 --> 00:14:06,720
For I can testify that they gave not only what they could afford, but far more.

197
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:09,950
And they did it of their own free will.

198
00:14:09,950 --> 00:14:19,420
In fact, they begged us again and again for the gracious privilege of sharing in the gift for the Christians in Jerusalem.

199
00:14:20,780 --> 00:14:24,480
Best of all, they went beyond our highest hopes,

200
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:33,400
for their first action was to dedicate themselves to the Lord and to us for whatever directions God might give them.

201
00:14:34,690 --> 00:14:38,750
So we have urged Titus, who encouraged your giving in the first place,

202
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:44,670
to return to you and encourage you to complete your share in this ministry of giving.

203
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:49,820
Since you excel in so many ways, you have so much faith,

204
00:14:50,340 --> 00:14:56,220
such gifted speakers, such knowledge, such enthusiasm, and such love for us.

205
00:14:56,220 --> 00:15:02,140
Now I want you to excel also in this gracious ministry of giving.

206
00:15:03,180 --> 00:15:08,200
I'm not saying you must do it, even though the other churches are eager to do it.

207
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:13,040
This is one way to prove your love is real.

208
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:21,680
You know how full of love and kindness our Lord Jesus Christ was.

209
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:27,250
Though he was very rich, yet for your sakes he became poor,

210
00:15:28,090 --> 00:15:31,270
so that by his poverty he could make you rich.

211
00:15:32,820 --> 00:15:36,120
I suggest that you finish what you started a year ago.

212
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:39,260
For you were the first to propose this idea

213
00:15:39,260 --> 00:15:42,400
and you were the first to begin doing something about it.

214
00:15:43,060 --> 00:15:46,620
Now you should carry this project through to completion

215
00:15:46,620 --> 00:15:49,800
just as enthusiastically as you began it.

216
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:53,320
Give whatever you can according to what you have.

217
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:55,780
If you are really eager to give,

218
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:58,560
it isn't important how much you're able to give.

219
00:15:58,980 --> 00:16:02,260
God wants you to give what you have, not what you don't have.

220
00:16:03,350 --> 00:16:06,890
Of course, I don't mean you should give so much you suffer from having too little.

221
00:16:06,890 --> 00:16:09,810
I only mean that there should be some equality.

222
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:14,570
Right now, you have plenty and can help them.

223
00:16:16,030 --> 00:16:18,910
Then at some other time, they can share with you when you need it.

224
00:16:19,470 --> 00:16:23,270
In this way, everyone's needs will be met.

225
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:27,440
Do you remember what the Scriptures say about this?

226
00:16:28,260 --> 00:16:31,240
Those who gathered a lot had nothing left over,

227
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:34,800
and those who gathered only a little had enough.

228
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:39,700
In that passage, Paul is describing

229
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:45,900
the giving of the Macedonian Christians for the Christians in Jerusalem.

230
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:53,510
And as you can tell from this passage, the Macedonian churches were extremely poor.

231
00:16:54,900 --> 00:16:58,080
But they begged Paul. I love that.

232
00:16:58,080 --> 00:17:03,060
They begged him, can we give to our brothers and sisters in Jerusalem?

233
00:17:04,820 --> 00:17:10,080
And Paul says that their heart is evidence that their hearts were totally sold out

234
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:11,940
and full of the love of the Lord.

235
00:17:13,890 --> 00:17:15,890
And so Paul wants the Corinthian church

236
00:17:15,890 --> 00:17:18,950
to be excellent in that area of giving as well.

237
00:17:20,110 --> 00:17:21,610
You see, giving is one channel

238
00:17:21,610 --> 00:17:23,820
where as we give to the Lord,

239
00:17:23,900 --> 00:17:25,840
the Lord uses that to bless others.

240
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:28,960
That's how we can bless others.

241
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:32,560
And God wants us to excel at that grace of giving.

242
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:35,720
It's part of our responsibility as Christians

243
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,980
to support the ministry of the churches

244
00:17:37,980 --> 00:17:40,520
and the churches begin to bless others

245
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:43,180
as well as ourselves.

246
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:47,960
The church can bless in a variety of fashions.

247
00:17:49,540 --> 00:17:52,960
It's a teaching place, teaching the scriptures.

248
00:17:54,020 --> 00:17:57,440
It provides resources for the hurting and the broken.

249
00:17:58,080 --> 00:18:02,760
It provides avenues for outreach and evangelism and mission.

250
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:09,040
The church blesses many people, and I trust that he's blessed each of you as well.

251
00:18:11,130 --> 00:18:12,910
And that's to be a motivating factor.

252
00:18:14,170 --> 00:18:15,910
We should want to do our part.

253
00:18:15,910 --> 00:18:20,150
We should want to continue to receive the blessings from this place

254
00:18:20,150 --> 00:18:22,890
and have others receive it as well.

255
00:18:23,940 --> 00:18:28,680
We do have a responsibility to give as brothers and sisters

256
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,960
that the church continues forward.

257
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:34,240
And you know this statistic.

258
00:18:34,420 --> 00:18:35,420
I share it with you again.

259
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,360
It pains my heart.

260
00:18:36,580 --> 00:18:40,760
But the reality is across our land, across the great United States of America,

261
00:18:41,180 --> 00:18:42,420
still this is true.

262
00:18:42,420 --> 00:18:48,080
that 20% of church members give 80% of the resources.

263
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:52,790
In business terms, we call it the 80-20 rule.

264
00:18:54,270 --> 00:18:56,110
And unfortunately, it's true in business.

265
00:18:56,470 --> 00:18:59,810
20% of your salespeople will give 80% of the business.

266
00:19:00,450 --> 00:19:04,470
20% of your leaders will take care of 80% of the production.

267
00:19:05,540 --> 00:19:09,510
And sadly, the church has the same statistic.

268
00:19:09,830 --> 00:19:13,370
20% of the people give 80% of the resources.

269
00:19:13,890 --> 00:19:19,130
Why should the church copy the world?

270
00:19:20,320 --> 00:19:23,100
Why should we copy the world?

271
00:19:23,460 --> 00:19:32,190
Why don't we be different and say 100% of our people give 100% of the resources to be different?

272
00:19:33,820 --> 00:19:34,400
To be different.

273
00:19:36,940 --> 00:19:38,420
In our church, we're actually better.

274
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:39,420
We're 70-30.

275
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,420
We can get better.

276
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:43,080
We can do better.

277
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:46,600
And here's one more sad statistic.

278
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:53,660
50% of church attenders don't give one penny to the kingdom of God at all.

279
00:19:57,930 --> 00:20:00,290
Yes, friends, we have a duty to give.

280
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,960
It's not a good motivation.

281
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:08,390
It's a little better than guilt, but there's still so much further we can go.

282
00:20:08,390 --> 00:20:13,470
But the reality is we need to give to continue the blessing of this place

283
00:20:13,470 --> 00:20:15,950
that it might bless you and others.

284
00:20:19,170 --> 00:20:25,970
The strength of giving out of duty, the money still comes in.

285
00:20:26,490 --> 00:20:27,490
Praise the Lord for that.

286
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:31,520
And responsibility is an admirable trait.

287
00:20:31,780 --> 00:20:35,300
If you're giving because it's the right thing to do, praise God,

288
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:38,700
you're moving forward in your motivation for giving.

289
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:43,170
The weakness, however, is it still can limit your joy

290
00:20:43,170 --> 00:20:50,020
because giving out of responsibility still doesn't ignite the fire of the heart.

291
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:55,560
Giving my wife treats on Valentine's Day

292
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:58,560
because Hallmark told me I have to do it

293
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:02,740
doesn't really fuel my fire, does it?

294
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:06,060
And you know what?

295
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:07,940
It doesn't fuel hers either.

296
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:12,220
But when I give because I want to,

297
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:13,640
because I love her,

298
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:15,260
because I want to bless her,

299
00:21:15,260 --> 00:21:18,460
and my love given to her blesses me back and others,

300
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:21,160
that's wonderful because I love her.

301
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:25,190
I give because I want her to be blessed.

302
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:32,300
When we give out of responsibility, we can get legalistic about it.

303
00:21:35,540 --> 00:21:36,100
I already gave.

304
00:21:36,180 --> 00:21:36,560
That's it.

305
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:38,070
One more appeal.

306
00:21:38,370 --> 00:21:40,590
Sorry, I've done my duty.

307
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:43,640
It's the wrong heart.

308
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:46,160
We get finicky.

309
00:21:47,940 --> 00:21:51,620
And still our hearts aren't soft to what God wants us to be doing.

310
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:54,520
Let's go to the third motivation for giving.

311
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:55,980
Giving to needs.

312
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:57,920
The third step up.

313
00:22:01,050 --> 00:22:03,290
It's the idea that I see this need in the church.

314
00:22:04,050 --> 00:22:06,190
I'm going to give to that because I like that.

315
00:22:06,910 --> 00:22:08,150
Ooh, I love that ministry.

316
00:22:08,410 --> 00:22:09,310
I'm doing that.

317
00:22:10,770 --> 00:22:11,950
I love the youth department.

318
00:22:12,450 --> 00:22:13,430
Man, they get my dollar.

319
00:22:15,330 --> 00:22:17,110
2 Corinthians 8.

320
00:22:17,710 --> 00:22:23,470
If you're really eager to give, it isn't important how much you're able to give.

321
00:22:23,830 --> 00:22:27,030
God wants you to give what you have, not what you don't have.

322
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:31,830
Of course, I don't mean that you should give so much that you suffer from having too little.

323
00:22:32,980 --> 00:22:34,300
There should be some equality.

324
00:22:34,460 --> 00:22:35,220
Remember this verse.

325
00:22:36,670 --> 00:22:39,090
Right now you've got plenty, and you can help them.

326
00:22:40,230 --> 00:22:42,350
We give that everyone's needs are met.

327
00:22:42,870 --> 00:22:46,410
Yes, the reality is we do want to give that needs are met.

328
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:49,040
But here's the issue there.

329
00:22:50,010 --> 00:22:55,110
At different times, we all see different needs to be met.

330
00:22:55,550 --> 00:23:00,750
And sometimes you'll see a need and realize that the church isn't doing something about that.

331
00:23:00,750 --> 00:23:05,010
And you get motivated to serve and to give in that area.

332
00:23:05,190 --> 00:23:06,210
And that's wonderful.

333
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,820
And that's a legitimate issue.

334
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:16,140
And the strength is when you see needs and you give to meet the needs, the needs are met.

335
00:23:17,090 --> 00:23:18,170
That's a good thing.

336
00:23:21,550 --> 00:23:32,370
However, if everyone gave just to needs that they saw, we'd still close down.

337
00:23:32,790 --> 00:23:37,830
Because we don't all see all the needs accurately.

338
00:23:40,260 --> 00:23:46,020
I realize, I realize in the age of suspicion of institutions,

339
00:23:46,740 --> 00:23:50,840
and it's easy to mistrust government and big corporations.

340
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:56,080
Look, Enron, you're all wondering, is corporate America just going down the drain?

341
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:58,040
And it makes me wonder.

342
00:23:59,630 --> 00:24:04,250
And with the scandal in the churches, you know, in a contemporary context and in the past,

343
00:24:04,250 --> 00:24:06,890
you begin to wonder, is this a crock?

344
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:10,800
And the government just blowing pork barrel spending.

345
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:13,640
I mean, we wonder, whom do we trust?

346
00:24:17,010 --> 00:24:17,850
Trust the Lord.

347
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:24,260
I used to want to give to projects only as well.

348
00:24:25,540 --> 00:24:32,160
I used to only want to give to projects because I could see my dollar immediately gratify a need.

349
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:33,920
And that made me feel better.

350
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:39,080
Because I'm not sure I trust those leaders and all that other stuff.

351
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:41,320
But I want to see that need met.

352
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:43,400
And I used to give like that.

353
00:24:45,570 --> 00:24:49,730
It's interesting now leading the church, the different perspective that I now have.

354
00:24:51,170 --> 00:24:52,810
Because we all have our passions.

355
00:24:53,230 --> 00:24:56,430
We all have our certain ministry that we favor over others.

356
00:24:56,430 --> 00:25:06,370
And let's be honest, many of us could care less about electricity, copy paper, liability insurance, and toilet paper until it's not there.

357
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:08,040
Right?

358
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:14,620
Who cares about the boring stuff until it's not there?

359
00:25:14,820 --> 00:25:16,700
And then we're up in arms.

360
00:25:18,780 --> 00:25:24,520
See, as we manage the church, we try and delegate monies to those different places

361
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:28,720
so that wherever you are, by the copier, it's there.

362
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:35,920
That we pay the insurance that in case somebody falls down, we can cover that, take care of you.

363
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:42,260
Toilet paper you can figure out on your own.

364
00:25:45,140 --> 00:25:49,440
If you gave only to special needs, we would close down

365
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:54,600
because we just don't get motivated on those bland everyday issues.

366
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:56,980
Heating and air conditioning doesn't sell.

367
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:00,340
Who wants to pay for that?

368
00:26:01,310 --> 00:26:02,210
But we need it.

369
00:26:02,870 --> 00:26:08,010
Because when the basketball league is cranked up and it's 99 degrees and swampy in there,

370
00:26:08,490 --> 00:26:10,150
nobody wants to come.

371
00:26:11,750 --> 00:26:13,630
And you don't want to be in there, and neither do I.

372
00:26:14,750 --> 00:26:17,790
And so we pay Edison to cool it down.

373
00:26:18,230 --> 00:26:19,310
And thank God that we do.

374
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:21,320
Makes ministry a lot easier.

375
00:26:21,780 --> 00:26:28,260
We must give to the church because the church is the heart of God's plan for reaching the world.

376
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:33,140
Even in the mundane parts of the church, it's still part of the bigger mission.

377
00:26:33,540 --> 00:26:37,220
Because through the church, the gospel is spread.

378
00:26:37,540 --> 00:26:39,920
Through the church, we reach the hurting.

379
00:26:40,260 --> 00:26:42,140
Through the church, we win the lost.

380
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:48,480
As well as dealing with the mundane realities of water, paper towels, heating, and cooling.

381
00:26:49,580 --> 00:26:50,500
It's all in there.

382
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:54,860
We can give to needs, but let's go even further up.

383
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:57,640
Let's give out of thanksgiving.

384
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:01,360
2 Corinthians 9.

385
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:06,080
You know how full of love and kindness our Lord Jesus Christ was.

386
00:27:06,740 --> 00:27:11,280
Though he was very rich, yet for your sakes he became poor,

387
00:27:11,860 --> 00:27:15,360
so that by his poverty he could make you rich.

388
00:27:16,390 --> 00:27:17,310
What's that implication?

389
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:21,520
God has given so much to you,

390
00:27:21,520 --> 00:27:25,260
and out of gratitude, out of thanksgiving,

391
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,140
we are to give back to the Lord.

392
00:27:28,540 --> 00:27:33,820
The strength of this position is it blesses the giver and the receiver.

393
00:27:34,280 --> 00:27:41,020
You see, God blesses those who give and remove that selfish root when you give out of thanksgiving.

394
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:53,760
The weakness of this is, friends, sometimes we're not always aware of all of our blessings, are we?

395
00:27:54,180 --> 00:28:00,970
If we only give out of the recognition of our blessings when we're having a hard time in life,

396
00:28:00,970 --> 00:28:04,310
it's easy not to see the blessings.

397
00:28:06,140 --> 00:28:09,600
And therefore our giving only goes on our emotional roller coaster

398
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:11,760
of how we perceive blessings.

399
00:28:19,110 --> 00:28:23,010
But friends, it's still better to give out of thanksgiving and obedience

400
00:28:23,010 --> 00:28:28,620
so we don't let our heart only dictate when we feel like giving.

401
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:32,240
But I want you to realize this.

402
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:37,820
Even if your life is difficult today or has been or will be in the future,

403
00:28:37,820 --> 00:28:42,440
we have a great God, we have a great church, we have a great

404
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:46,300
vision for this church, we've got a great building, we've got great people,

405
00:28:46,740 --> 00:28:50,380
we've got great passion for the Lord. These are good things.

406
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:54,340
And whether your life feels emotionally up

407
00:28:54,340 --> 00:28:57,580
or down, God is doing great things around here.

408
00:28:58,220 --> 00:29:03,780
And sometimes you may not see it because what one person

409
00:29:03,780 --> 00:29:07,660
over here gives ends up translating to somebody back here

410
00:29:07,660 --> 00:29:09,420
but you may not know it.

411
00:29:11,660 --> 00:29:13,560
But we as staff are dealing with all of you

412
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:15,620
in different ways and in other places

413
00:29:15,620 --> 00:29:19,280
and things happen outside of your own understanding

414
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:21,060
and you have to trust us.

415
00:29:22,850 --> 00:29:24,110
But I also want you to give

416
00:29:24,110 --> 00:29:26,830
because you know that God has blessed you

417
00:29:26,830 --> 00:29:28,310
and you want to give back.

418
00:29:28,510 --> 00:29:30,330
Even if you don't feel like it,

419
00:29:30,730 --> 00:29:32,730
friends, you have your salvation.

420
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:34,800
You have a community.

421
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:37,000
You have so much.

422
00:29:38,290 --> 00:29:39,050
You have so much.

423
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:46,720
But let us go to the final, I think the best motivation for giving,

424
00:29:47,300 --> 00:29:50,280
and that is to worship the Lord.

425
00:29:52,290 --> 00:29:54,670
2 Corinthians 8, you saw this earlier.

426
00:29:54,670 --> 00:30:03,350
They begged us again and again for the gracious privilege of sharing in the gift for the Christians in Jerusalem.

427
00:30:04,570 --> 00:30:07,150
Best of all, they went beyond our highest hopes,

428
00:30:07,150 --> 00:30:13,150
for their first action was to dedicate themselves to the Lord and to us

429
00:30:13,150 --> 00:30:16,930
for whatever directions God might give to them.

430
00:30:19,040 --> 00:30:25,740
Oh, friends, to worship, to say, Lord, you are worthy, you're worthy.

431
00:30:27,100 --> 00:30:30,770
Take my everything because you're worthy.

432
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:40,100
When you give from that motivation, when your heart gives to worship God,

433
00:30:40,100 --> 00:30:48,100
it is a blessing to you it is a blessing to the kingdom you become obedient and when you are

434
00:30:48,100 --> 00:30:56,620
obedient there is power and strength in being obedient and it becomes fun to worship god it

435
00:30:56,620 --> 00:31:04,380
becomes fun to give and allow god to use your gifts for whatever he wants but you're giving

436
00:31:04,380 --> 00:31:08,530
because he's great and wonderful and awesome.

437
00:31:11,050 --> 00:31:14,030
Oh, that we might be givers out of worship.

438
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:17,000
To give because God is worthy

439
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,800
and to give out of worship.

440
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:20,480
We can give from guilt.

441
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:23,100
We can give out of responsibility.

442
00:31:23,900 --> 00:31:26,120
We can give to needs.

443
00:31:27,260 --> 00:31:29,100
We can give out of thanksgiving.

444
00:31:30,730 --> 00:31:33,030
Or we can give out of worship.

445
00:31:35,490 --> 00:31:38,170
Which motivates you today?

446
00:31:38,170 --> 00:31:43,440
Where are you on the scale in your giving?

447
00:31:45,980 --> 00:31:49,720
Which one do you want to motivate you in the future?

448
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:56,730
What is the next step to make that a reality?

449
00:32:00,100 --> 00:32:01,640
Let me conclude by this.

450
00:32:02,700 --> 00:32:09,300
Let us be the church of God, trusting God with our lives and our finances,

451
00:32:10,140 --> 00:32:14,560
believing that God will use our gifts to further His kingdom,

452
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:16,820
to shape our lives like Jesus

453
00:32:16,820 --> 00:32:20,080
and to further His purposes in the world.

454
00:32:20,500 --> 00:32:21,700
If you believe that,

455
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:24,300
I would challenge you to give out of worship

456
00:32:24,300 --> 00:32:27,900
and let the Lord bless you and bless this place

457
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:30,750
and you will see amazing things happen

458
00:32:30,750 --> 00:32:33,570
when you give out of worship.

459
00:32:34,270 --> 00:32:34,770
Let's pray.

460
00:32:34,770 --> 00:32:39,790
Father, may we be a faithful community

461
00:32:39,790 --> 00:32:42,690
because You have been faithful to us.

462
00:32:44,560 --> 00:32:46,620
You have never let us down.

463
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:51,940
And so, Lord, we give out of thanking you for all that you are,

464
00:32:52,020 --> 00:32:54,460
for who you are, for your character,

465
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:58,440
and we do it, Father, to bless you.

466
00:33:00,850 --> 00:33:03,710
And then, Lord, may you take all of our gifts, our tithes,

467
00:33:04,190 --> 00:33:07,890
all that we give, and may you multiply those things,

468
00:33:08,430 --> 00:33:11,360
and may you spread that blessing around.

469
00:33:13,980 --> 00:33:15,480
So, Father, we trust you.

470
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:20,840
We trust you that you will take care of us if we give more than we're used to,

471
00:33:22,460 --> 00:33:23,680
but you've always been faithful.

472
00:33:25,810 --> 00:33:27,810
So stretch us in our area of trust.

473
00:33:29,470 --> 00:33:33,210
And stretch us, Father, in the area of our hearts and our motivation.

474
00:33:35,170 --> 00:33:36,410
Take us to a new level.

475
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:39,200
Take us up a couple notches, Lord.

476
00:33:43,340 --> 00:33:49,220
Refine us and mold us and make us more like your son.

477
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:52,780
Our gifts are yours.

478
00:33:53,650 --> 00:33:54,510
We are yours.

479
00:33:55,050 --> 00:33:57,880
And we love you.

480
00:33:57,880 --> 00:34:02,530
In Jesus' name, amen.

